came%20a%20full-time%20W2%20employee%20after%20years%20of%20being%20self-employed.%20I%20signed%20up%20for%20the%20highest-tier%20health-insurance%20option%2C%20the%20gold%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20meant%20my%20monthly%20premiums%20would%20be%20high%20but%20my%20out-of-pocket%20expenses%20would%20be%20low.%20I%20chose%20that%20on%20the%20recommendation%20of%20a%20nurse%20who%20told%20me%20that%20if%20you're%20having%20surgery%2C%20you're%20hitting%20your%20deductible.%20Choosing%20the%20gold%20plan%20would%20mean%20I'd%20pay%20less%20over%20the%20course%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20scheduled%20all%20three%20of%20my%20surgeries%20in%202019%20so%20that%20I'd%20have%20to%20meet%20the%20deductible%20in%20only%20one%20year.%20My%20total%20cost%20for%20all%20three%20surgeries%20was%20%245%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20I%20maxed%20out%20my%20HSA%20for%20years%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20I%20was%20self-employed%20for%20years%20before%20my%20surgeries%2C%20I%20opted%20for%20a%20health%20plan%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.healthcare.gov%2Fglossary%2Fhealth-savings-account-hsa%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehealth%20savings%20account%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20special%20savings%20account%20just%20for%20medical%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20HSAs%20because%20they're%20triple%20tax%20advantaged.%20Contributions%20are%20tax-deductible%2C%20even%20if%20you%20don't%20itemize%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ftaxes%2Fwhat-can-i-deduct-on-my-taxes%5C%22%3Etax%20deductions%3C%2Fa%3E.%20HSA%20earnings%20and%20withdrawals%20are%20also%20both%20tax-free%2C%20as%20long%20as%20you%20use%20the%20money%20to%20pay%20for%20qualified%20medical%20expenses.%20Fortunately%20for%20me%2C%20preventive%20surgery%20counted%20as%20a%20qualified%20medical%20expense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20maxed%20out%20my%20HSA%20for%20several%20years%20before%20my%20surgeries%20to%20lower%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ftaxes%5C%22%3Etax%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Now%20those%20savings%20were%20finally%20going%20to%20come%20in%20handy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20I%20wasn't%20on%20an%20HSA-eligible%20plan%20at%20the%20time%20of%20my%20surgery%2C%20I%20could%20still%20use%20the%20money%20in%20my%20HSA%20to%20pay%20for%20surgery.%20The%20money%20in%20an%20HSA%20stays%20yours%20no%20matter%20what%20kind%20of%20health-insurance%20plan%20you%20have%3B%20for%20many%20people%2C%20that%20makes%20HSAs%20better%20than%20flexible%20spending%20accounts%2C%20in%20which%20you%20have%20to%20use%20the%20money%20that%20calendar%20year%20or%20lose%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20I%20used%20my%20hospital's%20payment%20plan%20with%200%25%20interest%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20I%20got%20the%20bill%20from%20my%20surgeries%2C%20I%20contacted%20the%20hospital%20and%20asked%20whether%20it%20offered%20special%20savings%20if%20I%20paid%20my%20bill%20in%20full.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20old%20doctor's%20office%20gave%20me%20a%2020%25%20discount%20if%20I%20paid%20in%20full.%20But%20my%20new%20network%20didn't%20offer%20that%20%E2%80%94%20instead%2C%20it%20offered%20a%200%25%20APR%20payment%20plan%20for%20up%20to%2036%20months.%20I%20could%20pay%20my%20balance%20over%20time%20with%20no%20interest%20charges%2C%20and%20there%20was%20no%20fee%20to%20sign%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20signed%20up%20for%20that%20plan%20and%20chose%20my%20HSA%20debit%20card%20as%20my%20payment%20method.%20Every%20month%20the%20amount%20due%20would%20come%20out%20of%20my%20HSA%20account.%20Fortunately%2C%20I%20had%20enough%20in%20my%20HSA%20to%20cover%20my%20whole%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20looked%20into%20my%20hospital's%20patient-assistance%20program.%20These%20programs%20are%20usually%20designed%20to%20help%20low-income%20and%20middle-class%20families%20pay%20for%20medical%20expenses.%20Every%20hospital%20has%20its%20own%20income%20limits%20and%20rules%2C%20and%20it%20never%20hurts%20to%20apply.%20Unfortunately%2C%20my%20income%20was%20too%20high%20to%20qualify.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20great-aunt%2C%20a%20survivor%20of%20breast%20cancer%20herself%2C%20gave%20me%20some%20money%2C%20which%20reduced%20my%20costs.%20I'll%20always%20be%20grateful%20for%20her%20support.%20And%20though%20some%20friends%20encouraged%20me%20to%20start%20a%20GoFundMe%2C%20I%20knew%20I%20couldn't%20do%20that%20since%20I%20had%20the%20money%20in%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdid-things-make-my-preventive-mastectomy-affordable-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734386581000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67604e8927808b3289cd546a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdid-things-make-my-preventive-mastectomy-affordable-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22By%20scheduling%20all%20my%20surgeries%20in%20the%20same%20calendar%20year%2C%20I%20got%20the%20most%20out%20of%20an%20expensive%20health-insurance%20plan.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22zinakumok%40gmail.com%20(Zina%20Kumok)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A42%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdid-things-make-my-preventive-mastectomy-affordable-2024-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Where%20to%20watch%20Bears%20vs.%20Vikings%20live%20streams%20from%20anywhere%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20buy%20through%20our%20links%2C%20Business%20Insider%20may%20earn%20an%20affiliate%20commission.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-reviews-expertise-in-product-reviews%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELearn%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224802%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Keenan%20Allen%