E%3Cp%3EThe%20websites%20also%20provide%20data%20like%20aircraft%20type%2C%20location%2C%20speed%2C%20altitude%2C%20and%20operator.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221944%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20screenshot%20showing%20Flightradar24%20data%20of%20an%20American%20flight%20that%20took%20off%20from%20Newark%20on%20Monday.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67607a0c279d913c37cbae32%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221310%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20screenshot%20showing%20Flightradar24%20data%20of%20an%20American%20Airlines%20flight%20that%20took%20off%20from%20Newark%20on%20Monday.%3Cp%3EFlightradar24%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20also%20spot%20a%20commercial%20plane%20based%20on%20where%20it's%20flying%2C%20as%20airliners%20use%20specific%20flight%20paths%20when%20heading%20into%20and%20out%20of%20NYC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20large%20number%20of%20them%20fly%20along%20the%20New%20Jersey%20coast%2C%20so%20if%20you%20see%20low-altitude%20flashing%20lights%20in%20the%20night%20sky%20heading%20northbound%2C%20for%20example%2C%20it's%20quite%20likely%20a%20passenger%20airplane%20landing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlight%20paths%20can%20differ%20depending%20on%20the%20route%20and%20winds%2C%20but%20flight-tracking%20websites%20can%20give%20you%20the%20best%20idea%20of%20what's%20flying%20overhead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFederal%20regulations%20prevent%20commercial%20and%20recreational%20drones%20from%20operating%20too%20close%20to%20an%20airport%20or%20flying%20higher%20than%20400%20feet%20unless%20authorized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FAA%20will%20sometimes%20provide%20waivers%2C%20but%20its%20unlikely%20an%20aircraft%20operating%20within%20these%20parameters%20is%20a%20drone.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20drone%20activity%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fdrones-mystery-new-jersey-york-b37fda04755803392178b1f39b76ccd8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eforced%20a%20handful%20of%20airports%2C%20including%20an%20air%20force%20base%2C%20to%20close%20entirely%20%3C%2Fa%3Efor%20short%20periods%20of%20time.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221166b473-dda6-4099-b434-f3d68e47aa24%5C%22%3ESome%20hidden%20aircraft%20can%20be%20tracked%20via%20ADS-B%20Exchange%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20flight%20paths%20and%20tracking%20websites%20doesn't%20eliminate%20all%20of%20the%20potential%20aircraft%20that%20could%20be%20flying%20overhead%20%E2%80%94%20it%20simply%20identifies%20an%20aircraft%20as%20an%20airliner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20people%20can%20use%20a%20free%20website%20called%20ADS-B%20Exchange%20to%20filter%20for%20military%20and%20private%20aircraft%20that%20are%20blocked%20from%20websites%20that%20use%20FAA%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222624%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20screenshot%20of%20ADS-B%20Exchange%20LADD%20and%20PIA%20aircraft%20flying%20over%20the%20US.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67605ec5279d913c37cba270%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221316%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20screenshot%20of%20the%20ADS-B%20Exchange%20website%20showing%20aircraft%20using%20FAA%20programs%20to%20block%20their%20data%20from%20FlightAware%20and%20Flightradar24.%3Cp%3EADS-B%20Exchange%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20operators%20use%20specific%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftaylor-swift-elon-musk-private-jet-tracking-faa-reauthorization-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efederal%20programs%20called%20%26quot%3BLADD%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BPIA%26quot%3B%20to%20avoid%20flight%20tracking%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20they%20don't%20want%20their%20location%20data%20easily%20available%20to%20the%20public.%20Elon%20Musk%20and%20Taylor%20Swift%20are%20famous%20examples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20military%20aircraft%2C%20including%20drones%2C%20can%20turn%20off%20their%20ADS-B%20software%20to%20maintain%20stealth%20or%20secrecy%2C%20meaning%20they%20can't%20be%20seen%20using%20free%20and%20public%20websites.%20Drones%20with%20sinister%20motives%20%E2%80%94%20the%20kinds%20officials%20have%20said%20they%20aren't%20concerned%20about%20with%20these%20sightings%20%E2%80%94%20assumably%20also%20would%20not%20use%20public%20transponders.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20general%20aviation%20aircraft%20used%20for%20personal%20use%20%E2%80%94%20some%20of%20which%20are%20smaller%2C%20fly%20much%20slower%2C%20and%20could%20be%20mistaken%20for%20a%20drone%20or%20unidentified%20aircraft%20%E2%80%94%20are%20also%20not%20equipped%20with%20ADS-B%20and%20could%20be%20another%20unidentifiable%20object%20in%20the%20night%20sky.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b7771a57-f68b-48e7-be40-1648bbb5ec27%5C%22%3EDrones%20are%20quieter%2C%20with%20similar%20but%20different%20lighting%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20800%2C000%20commercial%20and%20recreational%20drones%20are%20registered%20with%20the%20FAA.%20There%20are%20a%20few%20easy%20ways%20to%20visually%20distinguish%20a%20drone%20from%20an%20airplane.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20drones%20and%20airplanes%20both%20have%20four%20lights%20%E2%80%94%20though%20lighting%20on%20a%20drone%20will%20usually%20be%20in%20a%20square%20pattern%2C%20while%20an%20airplane%20has%20lights%20on%20both%20wings%2C%20the%20nose%2C%20and%20the%20tail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224444%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20aircraft%20lights%20on%20a%20Frontier%20Airbus%20aircraft.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6760817dcf8d1359a2e03ccc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20aircraft%20lights%20on%20a%20Frontier%20Airbus%20aircraft%20flying%20at%20night.%3Cp%3ENicolas%20Economou%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20drones%20will%20also%20have%20red%20or%20white%20anti-collision%20lights%20for%20use%20at%20night%2C%20though%20many%20will%20be%20red%20and%20green%20for%20easier%20operation.%20The%20wing%20lights%20on%20airplanes%20are%20also%20red%20and%20green.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EObservers%20can%20use%20sound%20and%20movement%20as%20indicators%20if%20lighting%20doesn't%20help%20identify%20an%20airplane.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrones%20commonly%20hover%20or%20whip%20quickly%20in%20different%20directions%2C%20which%20are%20not%20characteristics%20of%20airplanes.%20Drones%20also%20usually%20emit%20a%20buzz%20or%20hum%20noise%20from%20their%20rotors%2C%20while%20passenger%20aircraft%20engines%20have%20a%20distinctively%20louder%20sound.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20FBI%20supervisory%20special%20agent%20Tom%20Adams%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2024%2F12%2F15%2Fus%2Fdrone-sightings-east-coast%2Findex.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3D%25E2%2580%259CI%2520can%2520tell%2520you%2520from%2Cat%2520night%252C%25E2%2580%259D%2520Adams%2520said.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECNN%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Friday%20that%20some%20of%20these%20reported%20drones%20could%20be%20people%20flying%20their%20own%20drones%20to%20hype%20up%20coverage.%20He%20added%20the%20sightings%20may%20have%20a%20simple%20answer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can%20tell%20you%20from%20my%20firsthand%20experience%20conducting%20operations%20for%20the%20FBI%2C%20as%20well%20as%20investigations%20into%20the%20suspected%20sighting%20of%20drones%20at%20critical%20infrastructure%2C%20it%20was%20fairly%20common%20for%20planets%2C%20crewed%20aircraft%2C%20and%20even%20low%20Earth%20orbit%20satellites%20to%20be%20misidentified%20as%20drones%20at%20night%2C%26quot%3B%20Adams%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fplane-or-drone-what-is-flying-overhead-flight-tracking-apps-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734383137000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F676083af27808b3289cd68b4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessi