%20sort%20through%20boxes%20at%20a%20Robotic%20Fulfillment%20Centre%20in%20England.%3Cp%3ENathan%20Stirk%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESen.%20Bernie%20Sanders%20says%20Amazon's%20focus%20on%20speed%20leads%20to%20%26quot%3Buniquely%20dangerous%26quot%3B%20workplaces.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20a%20new%20report%2C%20which%20Amazon%20disputes%2C%20Sanders%20says%20its%20injury%20rates%20are%20worse%20than%20it%20lets%20on.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwarehouse-nation-boom-ecommerce-jobs-2022-10%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%20is%20such%20a%20large%20employer%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20tilts%20the%20calculation%20of%20national%20statistics%2C%20the%20report%20finds.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EJeff%20Bezos%20once%20said%20Amazon%20would%20become%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-bezos-space-trip-compares-truck-driving-warehouse-work-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEarth's%20Safest%20Place%20to%20Work%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20Sen.%20Bernie%20Sanders%20says%20the%20e-commerce%20juggernaut%20isn't%20even%20the%20safest%20place%20to%20work%20in%20its%20own%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20sweeping%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.help.senate.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2Famazon_investigation.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Sanders-led%20Senate%20Committee%20on%20Health%2C%20Education%2C%20Labor%2C%20and%20Pensions%20(HELP)%20says%20that%20Amazon's%20focus%20on%20speed%20leads%20to%20%26quot%3Buniquely%20dangerous%26quot%3B%20warehouses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20report%2C%20which%20Amazon%2C%20in%20a%20response%20updated%20on%20December%2016%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aboutamazon.com%2Fnews%2Fpolicy-news-views%2Famazon-response-to-senator-bernie-sanders-report-on-workplace-safety%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edisputes%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20%26quot%3Bfundamentally%20flawed%2C%26quot%3B%20Sanders%20said%20the%20company's%20workplace%20injury%20rates%20are%20worse%20than%20it%20lets%20on%2C%20with%20nearly%20twice%20as%20many%20recordable%20injuries%20per%20100%20workers%20occurring%20at%20Amazon%20than%20at%20non-Amazon%20warehouses%20in%20each%20of%20the%20past%20seven%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20US%20employers%2C%20including%20Amazon%2C%20must%20report%20to%20the%20Occupational%20Safety%20and%20Health%20Administration%20any%20injuries%20that%20cause%20%26quot%3Bdeath%2C%20days%20away%20from%20work%2C%20restricted%20work%20or%20transfer%20to%20another%20job%2C%20medical%20treatment%20beyond%20first%20aid%2C%20or%20loss%20of%20consciousness.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20said%20that%20Amazon%2C%20in%20public%20documents%20and%20reports%20to%20the%20committee%2C%20%26quot%3Brepeatedly%20compared%20the%20injury%20rate%20for%20its%20warehouses%20of%20all%20sizes%20to%20the%20industry%20average%20for%20large%20warehouses%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20have%201%2C000%20or%20more%20employees.%20Only%2040%25%20of%20Amazon's%20warehouses%20have%20that%20number%20of%20workers%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20comparison%20is%20likely%20more%20favorable%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20injury%20rate%20for%20the%20subcategory%20of%20large%20warehouses%20is%20consistently%20higher%20than%20the%20overall%20injury%20rate%20for%20the%20entire%20warehousing%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20benchmark%20ourselves%20against%20similar%20employers%20because%20it's%20the%20most%20effective%20way%20to%20know%20where%20we%20stand%2C%26quot%3B%20Amazon%20said%20in%20response%20to%20the%20report.%20%26quot%3BPutting%20ourselves%20in%20a%20different%20category%20would%20be%20misleading.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20estimated%20that%20about%20two-thirds%20of%20large%20warehouses%20are%20Amazon's%2C%20and%20it%20employed%20nearly%2080%25%20of%20all%20of%20the%20workers%20at%20facilities%20of%20that%20size.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20although%20Amazon%20compares%20its%20rate%20against%20national%20averages%20compiled%20by%20the%20US%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20for%20a%20subset%20of%20the%20warehouse%20industry%2C%20the%20report%20finds%20that%20Amazon%20is%20such%20a%20large%20employer%20it%20tilts%20the%20calculation%20of%20national%20statistics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Amazon%20has%20promoted%20its%20success%20in%20bringing%20its%20reportable%20injury%20rate%20down%20since%202019%2C%20the%20HELP%20committee's%20analysis%20showed%20that%20year%20had%20an%20unusually%20high%20rate%20of%209.01%2C%20while%20its%20long-term%20trend%20has%20remained%20relatively%20flat%20since%202017%20between%206.54%20and%207.74.%20The%20overall%20industry%20range%20in%20that%20period%20was%204.8%20to%205.7%2C%20and%20the%20non-Amazon%20range%20was%203.17%20to%204.18%2C%20according%20to%20the%20committee's%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20attributed%20much%20of%20the%20elevated%20injury%20rates%20to%20Amazon's%20%26quot%3Bobsession%20with%20productivity%20and%20speed%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20it%20said%20drives%20workers%20beyond%20safe%20limits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20not%20a%20safe%20way%20to%20make%20rate%20without%20being%20injured%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20worker%20identified%20as%20RN%20told%20the%20committee%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20target%20number%20of%20items%20processed%20per%20shift.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20not%20a%20single%20person%20I%20worked%20with%20while%20I%20was%20at%20Amazon%20that%20didn't%20have%20an%20injury.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20safety%20progress%20is%20well%20documented%2C%20and%20we're%20proud%20of%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20said.%C2%A0%26quot%3BWe'll%20continue%20to%20invest%20in%20safety%20and%20continuous%20improvement%20for%20years%20to%20come%20as%20we%20work%20toward%20being%20the%20very%20best%20in%20the%2