cture%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fsoftbank-ceo-likely-to-announce-100-bn-us-investment-in-meeting-with-trump-124121601047_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Russia's%20%26quot%3BStarlink%20Killer%26quot%3B%20Might%20Become%20A%20Nightmare%20For%20Ukraine%2C%20Elon%20Musk%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20major%20concern%20for%20Ukraine%20and%20its%20allies%2C%20as%20well%20as%20US%20billionaire%20Elon%20Musk%2C%20the%20Russian%20Military%20has%20reportedly%20developed%20an%20advanced%20system%20which%20could%20detect%20and%20locate%20signals%20from%20enemy%20unmanned%20combat%20aerial%20vehicles%20(UAVs)%20that%20connect%20to%20satellite%20systems%20such%20as%20Starlink.%20The%20new%20Russian%20system%2C%20dubbed%20as%20the%20'Starlink%20killer'%2C%20is%20officially%20called%20the%20%26quot%3BKalinka%20monitoring%20system.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20States%20has%20provided%20a%20large%20number%20of%20Elon%20Musk-owned%20SpaceX's%20Starlink%20communication%20terminals%20to%20Ukraine's%20military%20after%20the%20escalation%20of%20Russia's%20offensive%20in%20February%202022.%20Ukrainian%20forces%20have%20been%20actively%20using%20Starlink%20to%20coordinate%20their%20military%20operations%20and%20connect%20with%20aerial%20and%20naval%20drones%20that%20Kyiv%20has%20been%20using%20for%20attacks%20on%20civilian%20infrastructure%20in%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbout%20The%20'Starlink%20Killer'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20state-of-the-art%20Kalinka%20monitoring%20system%20has%20been%20developed%20by%20Russia's%20Center%20for%20Unmanned%20Systems%20and%20Technologies%20(CBST)%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20by%20news%20agency%20Sputnik.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAndrey%20Bezrukov%2C%20chairman%20of%20the%20CBST%20board%2C%20on%20Saturday%2C%20claimed%20Russian%20forces%20are%20currently%20testing%20the%20new%20system%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20which%20can%20detect%20aerial%20and%20maritime%20drones%20up%20to%2015%20kilometres%20away.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20Kalinka%20system%20can%20help%20the%20Russian%20military%20to%20quickly%20detect%20and%20target%20Starlink%20terminals%2C%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20basic%20principles%20of%20radio%20signal%20transmission%20have%20not%20changed%20since%20the%20invention%20of%20the%20radio.%26quot%3B%20This%20could%20reportedly%20enable%20the%20identification%20of%20unmanned%20boats%20and%20the%20so-called%20%26quot%3BBaba%20Yaga%26quot%3B%20drones%2C%20among%20other%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Bezrukov%20claimed%20that%20%C2%A0Kalinka%20can%20even%20direct%20communication%20terminals%20from%20Starshield%2C%20a%20militarized%20version%20of%20Starlink.%20He%20explained%20that%20the%20new%20system's%20detection%20range%20is%20primarily%20determined%20by%20the%20terrain%20in%20the%20search%20area%20and%20by%20the%20use%20of%20other%20electronic%20systems%20by%20enemy%20forces.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERegarding%20the%20time%20it%20would%20take%20to%20start%20the%20mass%20production%20of%20the%20Kalinka%20system%2C%20Mr%20Bezrukov%20said%20that%20it%20would%20depend%20on%20the%20demand%20from%20Russian%20forces%20operating%20in%20the%20conflict%20zone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Is%20Starlink%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpaceX's%20Starlink%20is%20a%20satellite-based%20internet%20service%20that%20provides%20high-speed%20broadband%20internet%20access%20around%20the%20world.%20It%20operates%20by%20transporting%20data%20via%20light%2C%20similar%20to%20a%20fibre%20optic%20cable%2C%20using%20a%20constellation%20of%20small%20satellites%20in%20low%20Earth%20orbit%20to%20beam%20internet%20directly%20to%20users%20on%20the%20ground.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Starlink%20program%20aims%20to%20provide%20internet%20access%20to%20regions%20with%20limited%20telecommunications%20infrastructure%20and%20has%20proved%20instrumental%20for%20Ukrainian%20forces%20battered%20by%20the%20Russian%20offensive.%20Ukrainian%20military%20used%20the%20Starlink%20network%20to%20connect%20and%20fly%20drones%20to%20attack%20Russian%20forces.%20They%20also%20used%20it%20to%20send%20back%20videos%20to%20correct%20artillery%20fire%20and%20enable%20mobile%20networks%20with%20encrypted%20group%20chats%20connecting%20Ukrainian%20commanders%20to%20their%20soldiers%20on%20the%20battlefield.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734356940000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2F6okohkp8_starlink-twitter_625x300_16_December_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Frussias-starlink-killer-might-become-a-nightmare-for-ukraine-elon-musk-7262323%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20major%20concern%20for%20Ukraine%20and%20its%20allies%2C%20as%20well%20as%20US%20billionaire%20Elon%20Musk%2C%20the%20Russian%20Military%20has%20reportedly%20developed%20an%20advanced%20system%20which%20could%20detect%20and%20locate%20signals%20from%20enemy%20UAVs%20that%20connect%20to%20satellite%20systems.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Frussias-starlink-killer-might-become-a-nightmare-for-ukraine-elon-musk-7262323%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22NHPC%2C%20BEML%20partner%20to%20develop%20desilting%20solutions%20for%20hydro%20plants%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734356638000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fnhpc-beml-partner-to-develop-desilting-solutions-for-hydro-plants-124121601011_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Upon%20successful%20implementation%20in%20pilot%20projects%2C%20the%20solutions%20are%20expected%20to%20be%20replicated%20across%20other%20hydro%20power%20plants%2C%20further%20strengthening%