award%20in%20name%20of%20person%20he%20is%20said%20to%20have%20disrespected%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20interim%20order%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20said%20it%20remains%20%26quot%3Bmindful%20of%20the%20respect%20and%20honour%26quot%3B%20commanded%20by%20the%20memory%20of%20the%20late%20symbol%20of%20Carnatic%20music.%20The%20court%20also%20acknowledged%20that%20the%20articles%20penned%20by%20TM%20Krishna%20were%20%26quot%3Bhis%20way%20of%20conveying%20respect%20for%20singer%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20also%20noted%20the%20petitioner's%20claim%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20words%20used...%20are%20not%20in%20good%20taste%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20the%20award%20has%20been%20already%20awarded...%20we%20deem%20it%20appropriate%20to%20say%20Defendant%20No%204%20(TM%20Krishna)%20should%20not%20be%20recognised%20as%20a%20recipient%20of%20the%20Sangita%20Kalanidhi%20MS%20Subbulakshmi%20Award...%20and%20is%20also%20restrained%20from%20projecting%20himself%20as%20a%20recipient...%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20ruled%20for%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20said%20its%20order%20should%20not%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20comment%20on%20TM%20Krishna's%20musical%20abilities%20or%20as%20questioning%20the%20decision%20of%20those%20who%20conferred%20the%20award%2C%20including%20The%20Music%20Academy%20in%20Chennai%2C%20which%20is%20a%2096-year%20landmark%20institution%20in%20the%20field%20of%20Carnatic%20music.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Happened%20In%20Court%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20day's%20arguments%20began%20with%20Additional%20Solicitor%20General%20N%20Venkatraman%2C%20appearing%20for%20the%20petitioner%2C%20dismissing%20a%20claim%20by%20Senior%20Advocate%20CS%20Vaidyanathan%2C%20appearing%20for%20The%20Music%20Academy%2C%20that%20the%20petition%20had%20become%20pointless%20since%20the%20award%20had%20been%20conferred.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Venkatraman%20claimed%20%26quot%3Bnauseating%26quot%3B