ank%5C%22%3EDelhi%20Food%20Twins%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20on%20one%20visit%20to%20Mandi%20House%20that%20food%20consultant%20Taiyaba%20Ali%20stumbled%20upon%20a%20humble%20%3Cem%3Echai%20%3C%2Fem%3Estall%20right%20outside%20the%20Shri%20Ram%20Centre%20for%20Performing%20Arts.%20Here%2C%20she%20discovered%20the%20%3Cem%3Esamosa%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%E2%80%9CI%20found%20the%20place%20one%20winter%20evening%20while%20walking%20around%20Mandi%20House%20with%20my%20partner.%20It%20almost%20became%20a%20%3Cem%3Echai%20%3C%2Fem%3Esamosa%20date.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E2.%20Dadu%20Cutlet%20Shop%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLove%20at%20first%20bite%E2%80%9D%20is%20how%20food%20writer%20Parul%20Pratap%20describes%20the%20%3Cem%3Esamosa%20%3C%2Fem%3Eshe%20sampled%20from%20the%20eatery%20in%20Chittaranjan%20Park%20in%20Delhi.%20%E2%80%9CI%20grew%20up%20eating%20Punjabi%20%3Cem%3Esamosas%20%3C%2Fem%3Esince%20I%20was%20born%20and%20brought%20up%20in%20Delhi.%20But%20in%20the%20early%2090%E2%80%99s%2C%20my%20dad%E2%80%99s%20elder%20brother%20built%20his%20home%20in%20C%20R%20Park%20and%20I%20tried%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F80824%2Fsamosa-history-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBengali%20samosa%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Efor%20the%20first%20time.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fplugins%2Fvideo.php%3Fheight%3D314%26href%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.facebook.com%252FDelhiFoodWalks%252Fvideos%252F887935758613447%252F%26show_text%3Dfalse%26width%3D560%26t%3D0%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22314%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESinghara%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eas%20the%20samosa%20is%20referred%20to%2C%20is%20one%20among%20many%20gems%20at%20this%20eatery.%20The%20others%20include%20cutlets%2C%20%3Cem%3Etelebhaja%20%3C%2Fem%3E(fritters)%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Emughlai%20porota%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20flaky%20pan-fried%20%3Cem%3Eparatha%20%3C%2Fem%3Estuffed%20with%20meats).%20And%20accompanying%20every%20serving%20is%20ketchup%2C%20spicy%20green%20%3Cem%3Echutney%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20curd-based%20dip%2C%20and%20mustard%20sauce.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E3.%20Munni%20Lal%20Halwai%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Professor%20Pushpesh%20Pant%2C%20one%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20experts%20on%20Indian%20food%2C%20described%20the%20%3Cem%3Esamosa%20%3C%2Fem%3Eas%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccrude%20peasant%20dish%E2%80%9D%20once%20%E2%80%94%20he%20was%20referring%20to%20its%20ability%20to%20appease%20society%20at%20large.%20The%20moniker%20is%20attributed%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3Esamosa%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20no-frills%20recipe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20Munni%20Lal%20Halwai%20has%20been%20packing%20a%20punch%20in%20their%20%3Cem%3Esamosas%3C%2Fem%3E%20since%20the%201940s%20at%20a%20rate%20that%20won%E2%80%99t%20burn%20a%20hole%20in%20your%20pocket.%20And%20adding%20flavour%20to%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F295271%2Forigin-of-chole-bhature-in-india-partition-food-history%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20the%20classic%20is%20%3Cem%3Echole%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(chickpea%20curry)%2C%20onions%20and%20%3Cem%3Epudhina%20%3C%2Fem%3E(mint)%3Cem%3E%20chutney%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E4.%20Shri%20Bankey%20Bihari%20Samose%20Wale%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20Paharganj%2C%20there%20lies%20a%20shop%20that%20has%20been%20doling%20out%20delicious%20%3Cem%3Esamosas%20%3C%2Fem%3Efor%20over%2060%20years%20now.%20The%20%3Cem%3Esamosas%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehere%20hold%20the%20fancy%20of%20Ajay%20Raghav%2C%20a%20recipe%20curator%20who%20is%20always%20on%20the%20hunt%20for%20exquisite%20fare%20served%20by%20legendary%20and%20upcoming%20eateries.%20%E2%80%9CHere%20you%E2%80%99ll%20find%20crispy%20%3Cem%3Esamosa%20%3C%2Fem%3Efilled%20with%20flavoured%20mashed%20potatoes.%20They%20serve%20%3Cem%3Esamosa%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewith%20%3Cem%3Echole%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20the%20taste%20is%20just%20too%20good!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fsamosa-in-delhi-1-1732281135.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Shri%20Bankey%20Bihari%20Samose%20Wale%20is%20a%20legendary%20shop%20that%20serves%20Delhi's%20best%20samosas%3B%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fsamosa-in-delhi-1-1732281135.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fsamosa-in-delhi-1-1732281135-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fsamosa-in-delhi-1-1732281135-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fsamosa-in-delhi-1-1732281135-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fsamosa-in-delhi-1-1732281135-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-382208%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EShri%20Bankey%20Bihari%20Samose%20Wale%20is%20a%20legendary%20shop%20that%20serves%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20best%20%3Cem%3Esamosas%3C%2Fem%3E%3B%20Pictures%20source%3A%20(L)%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FC-CrFvFvdXU%2F%3Fimg_index%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFood%20Walk%20With%20Sanju%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20(R)%3A%20Ajay%20Raghav%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPointing%20out%20that%20the%20huge%20crowd%20garnered%20by%20the%20eatery%20owes%20to%20its%20proximity%20to%20New%20Delhi%20railway%20station%2C%20Ajay%20advises%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20best%20time%20to%20visit%20is%20winter.%20Do%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F287202%2Fgulab-jamun-indian-sweet-uttar-pradesh-food-history%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etry%20the%3Cem%3E%20gulab%20jamuns%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(Indian%20sweet%20made%20with%20%3Cem%3Ekoya%3C%2Fem%3E)%20here.%20They%20are%20silky%20smooth%20and%20warm.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E5.%20Rajesh%20Samosa%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20usual%20versions%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Esamosas%20%3C%2Fem%3Eare%20popular%2C%20their%20counterparts%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20the%20%3Cem%3Emaha%20samosa%20%3C%2Fem%3E(big%20%3Cem%3Esamosa%3C%2Fem%3E)%20and%20the%20mini%20%3Cem%3Esamosa%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%94%20have%20a%20comparable%20fan%20following.%20The%20latter%20finds%20expression%20in%20the%20menu%20at%20Rajesh%20Samosa%20opposite%20Scindia%20House%20in%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20Connaught%20Place.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnubhav%20Sapra%20of%20Delhi%20Food%20Walks%20stumbled%20upon%20it%20on%20one%20of%20his%20walks%20and%20since%20then%20has%20been%20an%20ardent%20fan.%20%E2%80%9CThese%20bite-sized%20%3Cem%3Esamosas%20%3C%2Fem%3Epack%20a%20spicy%20punch%20and%20are%20ideal%20for%20a%20snack%20you%20can%20grab%20on%20the%20go.%20Their%20crispy%20shells%20and%20warm%20fillings%20are%20perfect%20for%20an%20afternoon%20pick-me-up%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F8xWgyXlo9MI%3Fsi%3DpaS8eEkKQrgxDtVr%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20in%20the%20neighbourhood%2C%20Anubhav%20encourages%20you%20to%20wander%20around.%20The%20area%20is%20known%20for%20its%20gastronomy.%20Delectable%20evidence%20can%20be%20found%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3Echole%20bhature%3C%2Fem%3E%20(chickpea%20gravy%20served%20with%20Indian%20flatbread)%2C%20fresh%20fruit%20%3Cem%3Echaat%3C%2Fem%3E%20(street%20food)%2C%20cooling%20%3Cem%3Edahi%20bhalle%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20dish%20that%20combines%20fluffy%20lentil%20dumplings%20soaked%20in%20creamy%20%3Cem%3Eyogurt%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20topped%20with%20spices%20and%20%3Cem%3Echutneys%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F259515%2Findian-food-recipes-pakora-map-of-india-cuisine-history%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Epaneer%20%3C%2Fem%3Ebread%20%3Cem%3Epakoda%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3C%2Fa%3E(fried%20snack%20with%20cottage%20cheese).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E6.%20The%20Embassy%20Restaurant%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEmbassy%20is%20independent%20India%E2%80%99s%20first%20restaurant%20started%20in%201948.%20And%20food%20blogger%20Anushka%20Goel%E2%80%99s%20family%20are%20loyalists.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20parents%20introduced%20me%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3Esamosas%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehere%20when%20I%20was%20a%20kid.%20What%20excited%20me%20more%20than%20anything%20else%20was%20their%20size%3B%20they%20were%20so%20huge!%20I%20remember%20the%20first%20time%20I%20tasted%20the%20%3Cem%3Esamosa%20%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%94%20the%20huge%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F313009%2Fbengaluru-couple-nidhi-shikhar-start-samosa-singh-brand-of-crispy-chaat-snacks%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejumbo-sized%20snack%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20more%20than%20what%20my%20mom%20and%20I%20could%20finish%20together!%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fsamosa-in-