esting%20around%2026%20individuals%20as%20of%20July%2C%202023.%20The%20loss%20of%20habitat%2C%20human-wildlife%20conflict%2C%20and%20poaching%20have%20all%20contributed%20to%20the%20declining%20numbers%20of%20these%20regal%20predators.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20address%20this%2C%20a%20unique%20conservation%20programme%20has%20been%20launched%20in%20the%20park%2C%20aimed%20at%20safeguarding%20the%20Bengal%20tiger%20population.%20Supported%20by%20global%20conservation%20organisations%20like%20the%20World%20Association%20of%20Zoos%20and%20Aquariums%20(WAZA)%20and%20Busch%20Gardens%2C%20the%20programme%20uses%20technology%2C%20such%20as%20camera%20traps%20and%20geo-spatial%20monitoring%2C%20to%20track%20the%20tigers%E2%80%99%20movements%20and%20behaviours.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201600px)%20100vw%2C%201600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Forang_11zon-1732857998.webp%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Assam's%20Orang%20National%20Park%20is%20home%20to%20around%2026%20bengal%20tigers.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Forang_11zon-1732857998.webp%201600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Forang_11zon-1732857998-300x200.webp%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Forang_11zon-1732857998-500x333.webp%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Forang_11zon-1732857998-768x512.webp%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Forang_11zon-1732857998-1536x1023.webp%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Forang_11zon-1732857998-1200x800.webp%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Forang_11zon-1732857998-150x100.webp%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-ima